description: Returns a list of all ActiveMQ users.

parameters.name: BrokerId
parameters.description: The unique ID that Amazon MQ generates for the broker.

nested_items.name: BrokerId
nested_items.description: Required. The unique ID that Amazon MQ generates for the broker.

nested_items.name: MaxResults
nested_items.description: Required. The maximum number of ActiveMQ users that can be returned per page (20 by default). This value must be an integer from 5 to 100.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token that specifies the next page of results Amazon MQ should return. To request the first page, leave nextToken empty.

nested_items.name: Users
nested_items.description: Required. The list of all ActiveMQ usernames for the specified broker. Does not apply to RabbitMQ brokers.

nested_items.name: PendingChange
nested_items.description: The type of change pending for the broker user.

nested_items.name: Username
nested_items.description: Required. The username of the broker user. This value can contain only alphanumeric characters, dashes, periods, underscores, and tildes (- . _ ~). This value must be 2-100 characters long.
